pageContext.claim: “Who is he? [Rod Rosenstein] And Jeff [Sessions] hardly knew. He’s from Baltimore. There are very few Republicans in Baltimore, if any.”
pageContext.analysis: Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein previously worked in Baltimore, Md., which is overwhelmingly Democratic. But Rosenstein lived in Bethesda, Md., where there are Republicans but still is strongly Democratic. Rosenstein grew up in Philadelphia. Rosenstein was appointed by Republican President George W. Bush, but he has not identified with a political party publicly.
